# AI Trust Boundary

AI is an assistant, not an automatic author.

- AI-generated text must not directly overwrite drafts, outlines, characters, relationships, conflicts, or story bible fields.
- Generated results must first be stored as a pending proposal.
- User actions must include insert, replace, save as alternative, and discard when applicable.
- Replacement and restore operations must use a design-system confirmation dialog.
- Show enough context for the user to understand what the AI used.
- Quality suggestions must not directly rewrite chapters.
- Knowledge-base analysis should extract structure and technique, not imitate protected works.

